@startuml
title Slurm Maintenance Operator - Node State Machine

skinparam state {
  ' States for normal, in-progress workflow
  BackgroundColor<<inprogress>> #E3F2FD
  BorderColor<<inprogress>> #1565C0

  ' State for successful completion
  BackgroundColor<<success>> #E8F5E9
  BorderColor<<success>> #2E7D32

  ' State for failed operations
  BackgroundColor<<failure>> #FFEBEE
  BorderColor<<failure>> #B71C1C

  ' Decommission-specific states
  BackgroundColor<<decommission>> #FFE0B2
  BorderColor<<decommission>> #E65100

  ' Choice/branching states
  BackgroundColor<<choice>> #F3E5F5
  BorderColor<<choice>> #6A1B9A

  ' External/untracked states
  BackgroundColor<<external>> #F5F5F5
  BorderColor<<external>> #9E9E9E
}

[*] --> UNTRACKED

state UNTRACKED<<external>> : Node is active in partition,\nrunning jobs normally,\nnot tracked by operator

state entry_branch<<choice>>
UNTRACKED --> entry_branch : Operator detects node

entry_branch --> RESERVATION_PENDING  : [--enable-reservations]\nPhase 1: no existing reservation\nfor node
entry_branch --> PENDING              : [Phase 2: reservation is active]\nmark_node_for_reboot()

state RESERVATION_PENDING<<inprogress>> : Calculating reservation\nstart time based on running jobs:\n• No jobs → start now (T+1s)\n• Preemptable only → after longest\n  (or now if --terminate-preemptable-jobs)\n• Regular jobs → after longest job end\n• Mixed → after longest regular job

RESERVATION_PENDING --> DRAINING      : Reservation created\n(scontrol create reservation\nmaint-$USER:{node_name})\nstart_time, duration, user, account, flags

state DRAINING<<inprogress>> : Reservation is active.

DRAINING --> PENDING                  : [--enable-reboots]\nAll jobs drained, reservation active\nmark_node_for_reboot()

state PENDING<<inprogress>> : **RebootState.PENDING**\nQueued for operation.\nWaiting for capacity

state operation_dispatch<<choice>>
PENDING --> operation_dispatch        : Capacity available

operation_dispatch --> REBOOTING      : issue_reboot(node_name)\nscontrol reboot ASAP {node}

state REBOOTING<<inprogress>> : **RebootState.REBOOTING**\nOperation command issued.

state recovery_branch<<choice>>
REBOOTING --> recovery_branch         : monitor_node_recovery()

recovery_branch --> RECOVERING        : Node rebooting, checking BootTime

state RECOVERING<<inprogress>> : **RebootState.REBOOTING** (still)\nNode is down. Polling for recovery.

RECOVERING --> COMPLETED              : All recovery checks pass:\n1. BootTime updated\n2. monit healthy\n3. post_reboot_delay elapsed\n4. post-reboot hook succeeded\n\ncomplete_node_reboot()

state timeout_check<<choice>>
REBOOTING --> timeout_check           : Elapsed time >\n--reboot-timeout

timeout_check --> FAILED              : [attempts >= max_attempts]\nMax retries exhausted
timeout_check --> PENDING             : [attempts < max_attempts]\nReset to PENDING for retry

RECOVERING --> timeout_check          : Elapsed time >\n--reboot-timeout

state FAILED<<failure>> : **RebootState.FAILED**\nOperation failed after max attempts.

state COMPLETED<<success>> : **RebootState.COMPLETED**\nNode successfully rebooted/revived.

COMPLETED --> [*]

FAILED --> [*]


@enduml
